This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with learning-to-rank algorithms from implicit feedback, which is a common problem in information retrieval. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel learning-to-rank framework. Additionally, it could be classified under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as learning-to-rank is often used in natural language processing tasks. The paper also discusses fairness and bias, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
